Class IndexTorsion

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractTorsion
      • IndexTorsion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Immutable, java.io.Serializable

    public class IndexTorsion
extends AbstractTorsion
    Represents a torsion composed of atom numbers in a molecule.

    This allows the IndexTorsion to remain usable if the molecular geometry changes.

    Torsion is: index1-index2-index3-index4

    Torsion angle calculated between atoms 2 and 3.

    If moved, the convention is to hold atom1 fixed and allow atom4 to move.

    This class contains a pre-computed list of the atoms to be rotated and the rotation axis.
